Because I got a warning I looked at this: > Output created: Repl_plot-file.html > Warning message: > In doTryCatch(return(expr), name, parentenv, handler) : > supplied color is neither numeric nor character

I found a really old post (R 2.4 2007) (https://stat.ethz.ch/pipermail/r-help/2007-August/137848.html) that states this was a bug in lattice that should have been fixed. I loaded #lattice" but didnt close the warning.

Note that the last component fill is a factor (which isnot numeric nor character, at least in a zen kind of way). I presume you are somehow protecting col from becoming a factor, and that does not translate to fill.
